Knight of the League.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucailgrimheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cail Grimheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/15/01 1:07:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> And, yes, there are many reasons, but choose the one that is MOST important to you.<br>
<br>
There is ALWAYS a single most important one.<br>
<br>
I chose to be a shadowknight because of the combat potential, I work fairly well with my chosen profession's role, it comes fairly naturally. <br>
<br>
I chose to be human so that I would not get stuck in hallways as an ogre or troll.  I miss having the ability to slam things though.<br>
<br>
I chose the combination, feeling I can role play well with it.<br>
<br>
The first vote cast is my own. <p>Cail the Impatient<br>
Knight of the League.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueldritch05.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eldritch05</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/15/01 7:25:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I actually picked a Erudite cleric of Cazic-Thule because I love the city of Paineel.  I would have been a paladin, but there are no Heretic Paladins.  So I chose a cleric instead.  And it is definetly an experience being evil for a change.  Especially as a cleric; people don't seem to expect a cleric to be evil.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lavenia>Lavenia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/16/01 2:46:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I picked a wood elf druid (along with hundreds of others I know...) because I wanted this char to be more laid back from my others. Just to have more time spent wandering around when I wanted to, being mobile was very appealing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=mailto:LaveniaFV@aol.com><b>Lavenia</b></a><br>Circle of Sisters</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=castinareleas>CastinarEleas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 11:35:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> Modelled mine after a favorite PBeM AD&amp;D character, played the past 4 years.  Picked him because he was..quite unique, even in AD&amp;D terms (for those who are familiar, a grey-elf Ranger/Druid, favored terrain the Underdark) --- and because he's been so fun to play for that time, and he's been retired from the PBeM game (ended).  Had to continue on somehow, and this server came up, so... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
He has lots of ideosyncracies to carry over into EQ --- severe phobia of Undead (fun to RP during halloween events &lt;G&gt;), unswerving honesty...etc.  Lots of RP potential, lots of fun.<br>
<br>
Even built the story of his transposition from the FR to Norrath, where, once again, his past is catching up to him.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Castinar Eleas<br>
Ranger, on the 25th Branch of the Tree of Tunare<br>
Officer, Court of the Crosswinds <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 10:39:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I like monks ..</span><hr size=1> .. not for RP, but because I love pulling in EQ.  I've done wizard, warrior, and monk up to post-50 elsewhere and nothing is more satisfying for me than being able to lead a group anywhere and tearing up the zone from front to back (I especially like kedge, chardok, karnor's sewer, &amp; hate-plane).<br>
<br>
I'd have made a lizard monk, but they can't be neutral and I want to maximize grouping and (thus pulling) oportunities.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 7:09:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> Because Mommy was a Darkelf.. and I wanted to be a ShadowKnight, because I like RPing as one. <p><IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif"><a href="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo">Shintou Shinai</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle> #2 cutie ranger</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 8:19:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I play a halfelf ranger. I obviously didn't do it for stats. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I like to play halfelves, and in EQ what with the appearance options we're given I get to try my hand at playing a half dark elf.*shrug*  <p><center><b><font color="#710672" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea</font><font
face="arial" size="-1"> <br>
</b><em>Halfelven Ranger, Unkempt</em></font></p>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=karlea>Karlea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/11/02 1:21:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I've chosen the Iksar cause their character models looked pretty interesting and I wanted to play for the bad guys for a change, normally I always play goody-two-shoes characters. <p>~ Karlea, Trooper of the Legion of Cabilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/11/02 3:41:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I choose Iksar for a number of reasons. The biggest being I don't like any other race. I played EQ briefly when it first came out but quit because there was no race I wanted to roleplay. Came back when Iksar became available. <br>
<br>
Of course, I fell in love with them after playing them for awhile, finding their psychology, appearance, and history all very intresting. I don't find them evil at all really, just very different from myself. They continue to fasinate me.<br>
<br>
I picked a Shaman because I like to help other people, and the only &quot;help other people&quot; class available to Iksar was Shaman. Turned out to be the perfect class for me anyway! <p><img src="http://members.aol.com/bseh42/images/zilsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/Thumbnails/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 12:42:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I wanted to try something new (and I was tired of walking everywhere the slow way).  So I picked the race and class I've always been most annoyed with, and have always said the most obscene things about behind the screen, the one I always SWORE I'd never play...<br>
<br>
And let me tell you, it's been a tremendous learning experience.  I seriously recommend that kind of experiment to anyone who's been repeatedly annoyed by folks of one particular combo far more than all the others combined.  Sure, you might walk away hating them even more... or you might do what I did and end up falling in love with your character.<br>
<br>
I've even met a couple OTHER wood elf druids I've liked, too.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p align="center">
<img src="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/73377kimaya-sig.gif" width="381" height="100">
<br>
<a href="http://home.bellsouth.net/personalpages/PWP-TwilightBastion"><i>~ Click here to visit the Bastion ~</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/28/02 4:31:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why did you choose your race/class combination?</span><hr size=1> I am in touch with my inner gnome. I like pets that don't shed or rot. I believe the pinnacle of magical artistry is needing to rely on little but my own magic to survive - why own real things when I can summon what I need at a whim?<br>
<br>
